    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                <date>Decr. 26/47</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">My dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Some time<lb/> has elapsed since I have had<lb/> a line from you, I
                trust however<add>?</add><lb/> your silence has not been produ<lb/>=ced by
                indisposition &amp; that <sic>you</sic> health<lb/> has much improved.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Pray how did <persName>Mr Woolf</persName> manage<lb/> I noticed his
                passing through our city<lb/> but did not see him</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I reced. the last no of the Publication<lb/> Society, &amp; they
                have been distributed<lb/> you continue to send more nos.<lb/> to the orthodox
                Sunday School than<lb/> they have subscribed for.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I recd no Occident for <date>Nov</date> or<lb/>
                <date>decr.</date> for <persName>Miss Simpson</persName>, how does this<lb/> happen.
                Nor was there one recd for<lb/>
                <date>July</date>, please send them as she com<lb/>=plains &amp; perhaps would not
                pay her<lb/> subscription, for I tell them we do<lb/> not underwrite the mail.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Miss Seixas</persName> was married last
                    <date>Wednes<lb/>day</date> evening at 7 oclock Ours is a pro</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>gressive age. We <add>?</add>fully married<lb/> in the early part of the day,
                &amp;<lb/> we refine <del>
                    <add>?</add>
                </del> upon &amp; <sic>mary</sic> as near<lb/> the time for going to bed as
                decency<lb/> would allow.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We are to have another wed<lb/>=ding soon <persName>Miss
                    Tobias</persName> to <persName>Mr<lb/> Minas<add>?</add></persName>
                <add>?</add> I am apprehensive<lb/> there will be some difficulty about<lb/> who is
                to marry them, for report says<lb/> that he is one who has never been<lb/>
                circumcised. Do you know any<lb/> thing of it &amp; does it not prevent a man<lb/>
                from being married by a Jewish congregation<lb/> Is a man a <sic>jew</sic> altho his
                father &amp; mother<lb/> are Jews, when he is uncircumcised?</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Miss <add>?</add></persName> &amp; <persName>Miss
                    Peixatto</persName> are spending<lb/> the winter with us—I <del>thought</del>
                you<lb/> were going to visit us this winter</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">News scarce. Hoping this will meet<lb/> you well in which
                    <add>hope</add> I am joined<lb/> by mother sisters &amp; newphews—</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">Samuel Hart Sen.</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
